I have seen many different variations on duel solex set-ups from bay window
to early Okrasa and others. There are a few tricks to make them work and it
can be done. SCAT makes a steering carb linkage that could be used, and
equalizer tube between the manifolds will help , the hardest part I can see
is finding the correct air correction and emulsion tube.

Ronnie Go for it ray

pa. At 1 time Danny Zapada (I think it was him) was selling duel solex
manifolds he was having made. Look in the achieves on Everetts page

